sequenceDiagram
    participant A as User A (Browser)
    participant B as User B (Browser)
    participant SyncA as Sync Service Instance 1
    participant SyncB as Sync Service Instance 2
    participant R as Redis Pub/Sub
    participant DB as PostgreSQL

    A->>A: Types in Monaco editor
    A->>A: Yjs generates delta update (Y.Doc)
    A->>SyncA: WebSocket: send Yjs update

    SyncA->>R: Publish update to room channel
    R->>SyncB: Fan out to all subscribed instances
    SyncB->>B: WebSocket: deliver Yjs update

    B->>B: Yjs merges update into local Y.Doc (CRDT conflict-free merge)
    B->>B: y-monaco binding applies change to editor (no setValue() call)

    Note over A,B: Simultaneously, User B is also typing
    B->>SyncB: WebSocket: send Yjs update (concurrent edit)
    SyncB->>R: Publish update
    R->>SyncA: Fan out
    SyncA->>A: Deliver update
    A->>A: Yjs merges — both A's and B's edits present, no data loss

    loop Periodic snapshot
        SyncA->>DB: Persist current Y.Doc state to Files.content
    end
